Fodor and the six percent Hungarian
According to the communication of Gábor Fodor, Minister of the Environment and Waters, the meetings of professionals are coming to an end on Tuesday, however, Wednesday, after the official opening, the negotiations of the ministers on the international climate regime after 2012 will continue.
Experts and politicians from 192 countries around the world will discuss the Bali Roadmap that is supposed to define efforts to focus on the period of emission reductions set by the Kyoto Protocol until 2012.
At the moment, there are strong discussions on this issue between developing and developed countries.
The U.S. also reported that, for the time being, it did not want to discuss accurate figures, while they were ready to sign an agreement on the reduction, until 2020, greenhouse gas emissions of 25 to 40 percent from the 1990 level.
Another important topic of the conference is whether developed countries are committed, excluding emission reductions, to providing financial and technological assistance to countries that need it.
An agreement has also been signed on aid to be provided to developing countries.
The assistance fund defined by the Kyoto Protocol will be managed by a 16-member Governing Council probably under the UN Global Environment Facility (GEF), Piac és Profit (Market and Profit) reported.
The six percent of Hungary
On behalf of Hungary, Environment and Water Minister Gábor Fodor confirms the EU's ambition to retain its role as flagship in global efforts to protect the climate and to encourage the signing of the new international agreement before 2009.
The minister explained that the EU is committed to reducing its greenhouse gas emissions by 20 per cent before 2020 compared to the level reached in 1990, regardless of the successful signing of the "Agreement after 2012", and it was ready to reduce them by up to 30 percent if other major regions of the world and/or developing countries were also ready to make commitments adapted to their responsibility and capabilities.
Gábor Fodor recalled that in 1997, the signatory countries of the Kyoto Protocol had targeted a total reduction of 5.2 per cent and all 15 EU members of that time made a commitment on 8 percent less.
Hungary has committed to reducing greenhouse gas emissions by 6 per cent compared to the period between 1985 and 1987, our country will fulfil its commitment, recalls the press release of the Minister of the Environment.
The stakes are high in Bali because the long-term international agreement on climate policy must be put in place in the two-year period, otherwise the entry into force of the agreement would certainly be postponed after 2012. In this case, the reduction commitments below the values provided for in the Kyoto Protocol would not be immediately followed by a new international emission reduction system, the need for which was highlighted in the new report of IPCC, the international scientific body, which won the UN Nobel Peace Prize, which is responsible for addressing climate change.
The reduction in emissions would be delayed and the increase in the Earth's average temperature by more than 2 degrees Celsius could no longer be avoided which, according to scientists, would have extremely serious and irrevocable consequences.
The British Army is recruiting on YouTube
The units of the British army communicate, on the video sharing site, recordings made during its operations in Iraq and Afghanistan in order to make themselves popular.
First, it is the British Air Force (RAF) that has been passionate about YouTube: the special teams working in Afghanistan in charge of video footage of the operations against the Taliban since March 2006, the BBC announced.
These recordings, taken using miniature cameras mounted on the helmet, are checked at the headquarters of the operations of the air force in Kandahar and they are then transferred to London or the compatriots charge them on the Internet.
The political message is essential
Air force soldiers have already passed 139 footage on the net through this route and their "chain" has been watched by more than 75 thousand people.
The British defence minister registered under the name "defenceheadquarters" in the spring of 2007 and he is communicating videos about operations in Iraq and Afghanistan as the Commonwealth Office and the International Peacekeeping Forces in Iraq (MNFI) also have their own channels on YouTube.
Mission in Afghanistan
According to the initial objective of the Air Force, the videos were passed on the net to recruit. According to the defence minister, they were also used to make known to the general public the real objectives of the presence of the army abroad.
The propaganda published by this route costs virtually nothing compared to the usual recruitment commercials spent on television, the BBC Gordon Mackenzie, a defense consultant, told the BBC. On the other hand, it also inevitably carries a political message since it justifies in a special form the merits of the military operations decided by the government.
The Americans made a game
The army is stamped because, apart from the carefully composed and censored videos, amateur videos are passed on the sharing site that also present, for example, the death of soldiers: in the "official" propaganda films, a little hypocritical, the officers do not avoid talking about the losses but they never present the bloody side of the fight.
Moreover, many videos had already appeared on the net presenting the areas of operation in Iraq and Afghanistan that were carried out on a real mission, but the British army has only recently been racing for these videos.
The Americans do the recruitment a little differently using the America's Army shooting game downloadable for free. In this game the player can put himself directly in the place of the soldiers in the context of a more or less real simulation.
