Political Capital: Hungarian Guard has increased country risk
According to the Risk Analysis Division of Political Capital (Risk Analysis Division), the activity of the Hungarian Guard, constituted last August, with the support of the Jobbik Magyarországért Mozgalom (Movement for a Better Hungary) increases, in several aspects, the political risk of Hungary and the region.
In its “risk warning”, the company reports that, in relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard, the greatest political risk is already that “in the short term aggressive ethnic clashes can occur following the worsening of the already existing ethnic tension between the gypsy and non-Gypsy population of Hungary.”
The research institute added that the Hungarian Guard's political strategy, which is likely to provoke this situation, is the main reason for this.
As they say, this is explained by one of the main shortcomings of Hungarian political actors: "public actors have passed the public debate on the case of the Roma to the representatives of radical and extreme political groupings who have based a political strategy on the dispute between Gypsies and Hungarians."
The problem is aggravated, normal dialogue becomes impossible, extremists are strengthened and the arrival of aggressive conflicts is more likely, they say.
However, according to the research institute, under the effect of the increased attention of the Hungarian and international media the activity of the Hungarian Guard "has significantly deteriorated the image of Hungary abroad, in particular regarding confidence in the stability and democratic maturity of the country".
They recall that, following greater publicity given to the reorganization of Hungarian radical and extreme right-wing groups since the autumn of 2006, many associations have been formed in Hungary since the summer of 2007 calling themselves the "national association of self-defense".
"The common feature of these gatherings is that they define themselves as a civil organization while they publicly declare the preparation of their adherents to defense missions (disasters, national defense, defense of order), armed if necessary, moreover, by referring to the inability of the police, the army, in other words of the state," they added.
