The valley of Viňales in the west of the island is one of the most picturesque corners of Cuba.
Exhuberant vegetation grows on limestone soil.
Mogotes, limestone balloons and rocks rise in candlelight from the bottom of the valley, and, from the fertile earth having caught in their bowels, even its rotten rocks are covered with a very dense vegetable carpet.
