Ancient city founded shortly after the Spanish colonized the island.
It is the trade of slaves and that of sugar that have brought him glory and wealth.
The wealth has been embodied in the beauty and character of this small city city.
Koloniální španělská architektura,výrazně ovlivněná pozdějšími francouzskými osadníky, se za čtyři staletí téměř noseměnila.
Trinidad, located between the sea and the Escambray mountain range, is such a far-reaching place that still in the 50' years of the last century, there was no road that would connect this region with the rest of the country.
This isolation allowed him to stay aside.
We didn't build anything, and that's why we didn't tear anything down either, everyone was content to have a roof over his head.
If one has, in Trinidad, more time than an afternoon, then it is worth also going to see interesting places in the area, such as the beach Playa Ancón or the valley of the Sucreries.
Then, in the evening, it is customary to go to the Casa de la Música which comes alive after sunset and where the music only becomes deafen in the early morning.
Baracoa
Some designate this village located in the far east of Cuba as the most beautiful of the island.
This opinion is certainly already influenced by the path that leads to it.
The two roads that lead there since Guantánamo must cross high and rugged mountains and cross a landscape almost without marks of human activity.
UNESCO has inscribed the eastern pitfall of Cuba, thanks to its unspoiled landscape, on the World Heritage List.
We make the best chocolate, in the church, there is the cross of Christopher Columbus (in reality, it was born about a hundred years after the journey of Columbus) and from the hill where the old castle and the current hotel El Castillo stand, we see several mountains table, the most famous of which is El Yunque.
About coffee, rum, cigars, the Sierra Maestra mountain range, the Bay of Sows and Isla de Pinos Island, the Tropicana cabaret, the sanctuary of the patron saint of Cuba Caridad del Cobre, the Santeria, African religions practiced by the descendants of the former slaves, about all this one could fill a number of pages.
