Congress approves the transposition of the Mifid, which came into force on November 1
In parallel with its parliamentary formality, which ended today with the Congressional vote amendments incorporated into the draft in the Senate, the Government has submitted to a public hearing the regulations that will develop the new law, with the objective of its entry into force before the year ends.
Representatives of the various groups agreed to highlight the effort made by Members of Parliament and senators to negotiate and make the best regulation to ensure investor protection and to regulate in detail the activities of the agencies to ensure that markets function effectively.
The Mifid, which amends the Securities Market Law, involves the modernization of financial markets, at a time when it strengthens investor protection, improves the powers of the leaders of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and promotes cooperation between the various leaders of the European Union.
The new regulations will provide financial consulting services to both specialized social reasons and to natural or legal persons and create a new type of financial services (ESIS), financial consulting companies (FIAs), which merge with securities companies, securities agencies and holding companies.
In addition, it increases the number of systems for the execution of transactions on financial instruments, so that it is possible to add to the regulated secondary markets multilateral trading systems and internationalization systems of orders, which compete with the current stock exchange managers.
The Act also requires investment service companies to disclose information on key aspects of its business profile, risk exposure and forms of risk management on the market and requires them to keep a record of all transactions they carry out, to facilitate control by the NVC.
Through the Congressional Economics Commission, several amendments have been added, including one that highlights that tenured debts will be considered a "complex" financial instrument given its high risk to the investor, which has demonstrated with what has happened with the debt of high-risk American mortgages (subprime).
In addition, they took advantage of the transposition of management took the opportunity to legally delineate the functions that graduates in Economics may have 30 years after 1977, the royal decree, which delimits the professional functions reserved for economists.
For its part, the Senate has incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as that of the mediator, who will work on behalf of a company, who will not require the authorization of the CNMV and who will be able to lend his services of marketing of products and attract new clients to different investment companies at the same time.
