What assurance is right for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the face of possible claims, involves a significant expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, gender, seniority of the driver's license, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or use of it, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
There is that, escoger el seguro de automóvil adecuado es incluso más difícil que elegir el modelo de vehículo.
And it is that, choosing the right car insurance, is even more difficult than choosing the model of the vehicle.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is reflected in an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium granted and in exchange it becomes responsible for the obligation to pay the compensation in the event of a claim.
The premium is the price of insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, seniority of the driver's licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or used, including.
Insurance companies make their prices based on statistics, so that the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the rating.
It is for this reason that people over 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, since statistics show that these people have a lower claim rate due to their caution.
Similarly, by using censuses, the companies concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency, and therefore the probability of having an accident.
By increasing the frequency the probabilities increase.
There are many of the variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
That is why the driver must study the situation to choose the car insurance that best adapts to his profile.
Here we will expose the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face various drawbacks when entering into a contract with insurance at an affordable price, as can be the low experience in driving and seniority of the driver's license.
While the ideal way to be well insured is insurance at all risks, other more economical options exist.
The most predictive drivers can opt for any deductible risk insurance, so that they get coverage from insurance at all risks but at a more affordable price.
This form of agreement implies that the customer pays part of the amount of the claim.
"The part of the amount of the loss that the customer pays will be established according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the amount will be lower," says Luis Noguera, the head of First Europa, online insurance mediator in Spain.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer provides protection to deal with damage to third parties, but for those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fires and loss of the vehicle.
Advice.
If you are a 25-year-old minor, try to be careful and avoid claims where possible, since it will affect the bonus, which can reduce the price of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the basic rate that the company has.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic tariff.
"The subsidies and sanctions will depend on the company and the profit of it.
If the company has had a good year it will be able to afford to increase the bonuses, "says Noguera.
Beyond the age of 25, it becomes easier for drivers when making a contract with insurance, since the claim rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
It is therefore better to choose insurance any risk with deductible.
"Normally young people cannot benefit from the experience gained beforehand after an accident," says the director of the European company in Spain and adds that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the 'fear of the novice' has passed.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children it is preferable that he negotiates insurance at all risks, as long as his economic situation allows him.
Child marriages are considered by insurers to be the people with the lowest loss rate, because the increases will be lower.
In this case the best insurance would be insurance at all risks with deductible (possibly of 300 euros), or an insurance with an extended third party from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured has a high level of bonus.
“They have more casual driving and they have greater purchasing power to afford the luxury of taking on a larger amount of franchises,” Noguera said.
For retirees, insurance at all risks with deductible is preferable (by being this one of 150 euros), or an insurance to extended third party when the insurer has a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible claims, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is why it is fundamental to properly study the insurance that suits us most according to our personal situation.
